<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRITISH BOY'S SCHOOL SAYS IT'S TOO MACHO FOR GIRLS, SCRAPS COEDUCATION PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A British boys' school run by Roman Catholic monks has scrapped an experiment 
in admitting girls, saying its sporty regimen was too macho for them. 
</P>
<P>
Belmont Abbey School, near Hereford in western England, has become the first 
British fee-paying school to return to single-sex status after becoming 
coeducational. 
</P>
<P>
"We took the decision on educational grounds. There was no scandal, no 
pregnancies and we are not misogynists," headmaster Father Christopher Jenkins 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
